  "question": "Are Best Buy's gross margins historically consistent (not fluctuating more than roughly 2% each year)? If gross margins are not a relevant metric for a company like this, then please state that and explain why.",
  "answer": "Yes, Best Buy's gross margins are historically consistent based on the available data, with fluctuations of less than 2%. According to the consolidated performance summary, the gross profit as a percentage of revenue was 22.4% in fiscal 2021, 22.5% in fiscal 2022, and 21.4% in fiscal 2023 [PAGE 25]. The year-over-year change was 0.1% from fiscal 2021 to fiscal 2022, and a decline of 1.1% from fiscal 2022 to fiscal 2023.\n\nIt should be noted that the document states Best Buy's gross profit rate and SG&A rate may not be comparable to other retailers because of varying methods for recording supply chain costs [PAGE 25].",
